§ 4754. LIMITATION ON PRIOR AUTHORIZATION REQUIREMENTS
(a) A health insurance plan shall not require prior authorization for
prescription drugs for a patient who is receiving medication-assisted treatment
medication for opioid use disorder if the dosage prescribed is within the U.S.
Food and Drug Administration’s dosing recommendations.
